is supposed to be neutral!

136
00:06:43,458 --> 00:06:46,083
Ooh, neutral magic, eh?
He's catching on pretty fast.

137
00:06:46,166 --> 00:06:49,166
Uh-huh. Not just anybody
would blurt that out.

138
00:06:49,250 --> 00:06:52,083
I'm sorry I was late.
I was building a sandcastle.

139
00:06:52,166 --> 00:06:54,000
[KAZAMA]
How old are you?

140
00:06:54,083 --> 00:06:56,125
Which explains why my
hands are covered with dirt.

141
00:06:56,208 --> 00:06:57,750
Hence, earth elemental.

142
00:06:57,833 --> 00:06:59,333
Well, that clears that up!

143
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:03,791
I've got to make
a run for it.

144
00:07:03,875 --> 00:07:06,458
[YOKOSHIMA] Yo, Kenji!
Wanna drumstick?

145
00:07:06,541 --> 00:07:09,041
[NAGAYAMA] Check me
while I sink this shot!

146
00:07:09,125 --> 00:07:10,333
[KAZAMA] 'Cept I can't
just leave 'em here

147
00:07:10,416 --> 00:07:11,625
with these crazies.

148
00:07:11,708 --> 00:07:13,375
If you're trying to
banish the guy's memory,

149
00:07:13,458 --> 00:07:14,666
I don't think it's working.

150
00:07:14,750 --> 00:07:16,791
Yeah, no kidding.

151
00:07:16,875 --> 00:07:18,458
I know. We'll launch an attack

152
00:07:18,541 --> 00:07:21,916
comprised of all our
elements working in tandem!

153
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:24,833
[KAZAMA] This is
not gonna end well.

154
00:07:24,916 --> 00:07:28,666
[NAGAYAMA &amp; YOKOSHIMA]
We'll always be best friends!

155
00:07:28,750 --> 00:07:30,416
